NOTES: Recorded simultaneously by Gerrit Vyn using 30"Roche parabola with MKH20.  I used the filter on the Telinga Pro 5W stereo parabola from the beginning until 14:20.  After the break at 14:20, I turned the filter off.  This is easily visible on the waveform.  First female vocalizations start at 28:43.  They are high-pitched and more staccato than the male vocalizations. Sound stimulation was (other): Human approach to nest.. Other Behaviors: Mob, Scold. Habitat: Tundra, Arctic Tundra, Creek.
